'''Docking Bay 17''', also referred to as '''Hangar Bay 17''', was a cavernous docking bay located in the central hub of [[Exis Station/Legends|Exis Station]]. It was one of several docking bays programmed by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Jedi historian|historian]] [[Tionne Solusar]] to respond only to the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi's]] signal.

In [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]], during the [[Mission to Exis Station]], Tionne and her companions [[Anakin Solo]], [[Tahiri Veila]], [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], and Master [[Ikrit]] docked the ship ''[[Lore Seeker]]'' in Docking Bay 17. While the Jedi and [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] exited the bay, at least eight of "[[Prophet of the Dark Side|Mage]]" [[Orloc]]'s [[Droid/Legends|droids]] attacked them with [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]]. As the Jedi attempted to escape via a metal mesh walkway, Tahiri's blond hair snagged in the floor grating. Unable to pull herself free, Tahiri was saved by a swipe from Tionne's [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]]. The Jedi quickly left the hangar and closed the [[Blast door/Legends|blast doors]] behind them. However, R2's attempt to scramble the locks did not hold the pursuing droids for long; in the end, R2 gave himself up so that his companions could escape.

